In adults, red bone marrow is primarily found in the flat bones, such as the pelvic girdle and the sternum. In children, it is found in the medullary cavity of the long bones, such as the femur. The red bone marrow contains hematopoietic cells, which are responsible for generating red blood cells.In infants, almost the entire bone cavity is filled with red bone marrow and fully proliferating blood cells. Even the fingers have some hematopoiesis occurring.he red bone marrow contains hematopoietic cells, which are responsible for generating red blood cells. In infants, almost the entire bone cavity is filled with red bone marrow and fully proliferating blood cells. Even the fingers have some hematopoiesis occurring.
